        "text": ", etc. (see our vers. 3, 4). What Hezekiah \"stopped\" was the spring, or more strictly access to it, and guided its prized waters down, probably by an underground channel, to Siloam, or else to the pool in the city which he had constructed and enclosed by that \"another wall without\" (ver. 5), west of the \"city of David.\" 2 Chronicles 32:30",
